    <item>
      <title>TIL: TMUX pane management</title>
      <link>https://pawka.notrollsallowed.com/posts/2019-09-25/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 25 Sep 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://pawka.notrollsallowed.com/posts/2019-09-25/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;:til: :tmux:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Inside any pane, press &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;Prefix&amp;gt;!&lt;/code&gt; and tmux will create a new window from your&#xA;pane, removing the original pane.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Now, to move the first window into a pane in the second window, press&#xA;&lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;Prefix&amp;gt;:&lt;/code&gt; to enter Command mode, and type this:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-viml&#34; data-lang=&#34;viml&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;:&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;join&lt;/span&gt;-&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;pane&lt;/span&gt; -&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;s&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;panes&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-viml&#34; data-lang=&#34;viml&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;:&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;join&lt;/span&gt;-&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;pane&lt;/span&gt; -&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;s&lt;/span&gt; :&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;You can use this technique to move panes around as well. If your first window&#xA;had two panes, you could specify the source pane like this:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
