      <guid>https://pawka.notrollsallowed.com/posts/2019-09-24/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;:til: :tmux:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Tmux has a handy shortcut that copies the entire visible contents of a pane to&#xA;a paste buffer. Enter tmuxâ€™s Command mode with &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;Prefix&amp;gt;:capture-pane&lt;/code&gt;.&#xA;The contents of the pane will be in a paste buffer. You can then paste that&#xA;content into another pane or window by pressing &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;Prefix&amp;gt;]&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
